# âœ… Sprint Testing Checklist â€“ Login Feature

This document outlines the sprint testing checklist for a **Login Feature** as part of Agile & Scrum Week 2 assignment.

---

## ðŸ”¹ 1. Requirement Review
- [ ] Review user stories and acceptance criteria for login feature  
- [ ] Confirm inputs (email/username, password) and expected behavior  
- [ ] Validate error messages and edge cases listed in user story  
- [ ] Clarify dependencies (e.g., API, backend, database)  

---

## ðŸ”¹ 2. Test Planning
- [ ] Identify test scenarios (positive and negative cases)  
- [ ] Write test cases for functional, UI, security, and performance  
- [ ] Review test cases with Product Owner or Scrum Team  
- [ ] Add test cases to the sprint board (e.g., Jira, Trello)  

---

## ðŸ”¹ 3. Environment Setup
- [ ] Confirm test environment is stable and up-to-date  
- [ ] Ensure test data (valid/invalid users) is prepared  
- [ ] Verify API endpoints and database access  

---

## ðŸ”¹ 4. Functional Testing
- [ ] Login with valid username and password  
- [ ] Login with invalid username and/or password  
- [ ] Check field validations (empty inputs, invalid email format)  
- [ ] Verify forgot password link works  
- [ ] Test login button functionality and form submission  

---

## ðŸ”¹ 5. UI/UX Testing
- [ ] Check layout consistency across devices/browsers  
- [ ] Verify placeholder text, button labels, and icons  
- [ ] Ensure error messages are user-friendly and correctly placed  

---

## ðŸ”¹ 6. Security Testing
- [ ] Test for SQL injection in input fields  
- [ ] Check password is masked while typing  
- [ ] Validate password not stored or visible in browser cache  
- [ ] Attempt brute force login to ensure rate-limiting or lockout  

---

## ðŸ”¹ 7. API Testing
- [ ] Send login request with valid/invalid data  
- [ ] Verify response codes (200, 401, 400)  
- [ ] Confirm token/session creation on successful login  

---

## ðŸ”¹ 8. Regression Testing
- [ ] Ensure login does not break existing functionality  
- [ ] Test navigation to login from different parts of the app  

---

## ðŸ”¹ 9. Exploratory Testing
- [ ] Perform ad-hoc testing with unexpected inputs or actions  
- [ ] Test login with network delay or slow performance  

---

## ðŸ”¹ 10. Test Reporting & Review
- [ ] Log defects with clear steps and screenshots  
- [ ] Track testing progress in daily standups  
- [ ] Update test cases based on feedback/changes  
- [ ] Participate in sprint review/demo and share test results  
